{
  "texts": [
    "Each type of attack strategy utilizes a dedicated prompt template for query modification.",
    "The details for strategy design are in Appendix A.7.",
    "A complete GS-MCTS process includes the following steps: action selection, state expansion & evaluation, and backpropagation, which is defined as a \"search cycle\".",
    "For example, given any query p, we perform N m search cycles, and each cycle adds a new node state s ← p, q, ô, ĵ, where q is the set of modified queries from M A, ô is the set of answers corresponding to any modified query from M D, and ĵ",
    "is the set of judgments given by J A."
  ]
}